pr_body: Replaced Eclipse IDE with VS Code IDE on the website.

=>Formatted the OmniFish-JEE10 branch using NetBeans IDE and the Google-java-format tool, following the instructions in the Readme.md file of the master branch. This step ensures consistent code formatting.

=>Upgraded OmniFish-JEE10 to be compatible with Payara 6 and Jakarta EE 10. This might involve updating libraries, APIs, and configurations to match the new versions.

=>Deployed and ran the Cargo Tracker application using traditional methods:

          IDE: Visual Studio Code
          Command line: Used "mvn clean package cargo:run" to build and run the application using Maven and Cargo.

=>Resolved the data source error, which might have involved fixing configuration issues related to the data source used by the application.

=>Removed unnecessary dependencies that are not required for the Payara server. This helps optimize the application's size and performance.

=>Updated and synchronized all the changes from the master branch, making sure they are compatible with Jakarta EE 10 and Payara 6. This step ensures that the OmniFish-JEE10 branch is up-to-date with the latest changes from the master branch.

=>Cleaned and properly aligned code lines for better readability and comparability with the master branch. Consistent formatting and proper code alignment improve code maintainability and collaboration.

Overall, these steps have helped bring the OmniFish-JEE10 branch in line with the latest technologies and updates, making it compatible with Payara 6 and Jakarta EE 10.
